item.title: Hipster Horns Sound Pack
item.dc:creator: akabillposters
item.description:
Some of the new horns use Shape to add pressure, so you might be able to get reasonably close by layering them with sounds like Lobster (The Future) and some lower octave resonant sounds like some of those in the Game Waves pack and/or Crook (Disturbing Leads).

Failing that, you could just bring it in as a sample. Especially as trap horns often aren‚Äôt used with any great complexity.

Just a thought.

item.description:
Fredrik:

All: We‚Äôre in the process of planning the next couple of months, so I‚Äôll be on the lookout for pack ideas!

In terms of ideas, I have two very specific ones.

The first and possibly more possible one would be to work with a producer like RAC again to bring some more retro and analogue-sounding synthesizer sounds into the Auxy lineup.

The second idea would be to allow some of the producers from the community well-versed in sound design, such as BlackOcean, develop a pack for the app. I‚Äôve already reached out to you about this in the past, but still haven‚Äôt received any sort of response/acknowledgement. Regardless of that, there are some seriously talented sound designers on the forum here that would help expand the Auxy sound library for free if you would be willing to let us do so.

I think users can still make something jazzy outta that sax, but I really appreciate the sentiment behind prioritising raw, orchestra instruments. Before I knew how to do a siiick beat, I was trying to make things that sounded like movie soundtracks!

item.title: Hipster Horns Sound Pack
item.dc:creator: Fredrik
item.description:
Good feedback! We launched with perhaps the highest possible sampling quality (Nicklas Flyckt is one of the best) which is a bar we know we just can‚Äôt beat every month.

That being said, I think regarding this pack you were also expecting more of a jazzy solo pack. These instruments are more orchestral and most sounds are brass sections (not solo recordings). This makes them great for backgrounds, movie scores, ambient, chill etc. but not ideal for jazz.

What label a pack is released under is more of a contract thing and not really worth reading much into :). We still collaborate with sample providers and artists for the packs.

All: We‚Äôre in the process of planning the next couple of months, so I‚Äôll be on the lookout for pack ideas!

(Please use the forum instead of PM‚Äôing me! )
